@joernchen we were discussing the possibility of just not supporting web console on Rails versions < 4.2.  Backporting that commit seems fine, but just saying "we don't support this" sounds like less of a maintenance / security burden on us.

Of course saying "we don't support this" means we'll do a security release that specifically raised an exception for people trying to use web console in older versions of Rails.  What do you think?

@rafaelfranca: is what I'm saying accurate?

